description: Bridgeman Concrete have been providing concrete to New Zealanders for over 50 years in the Upper North Island. New partners were welcomed in Tauranga in 2018 and resulted in the MixUp Concrete brand being established. Both companies are strong, independent and family-owned, with their continuous growth evidence of a successful focus on customer satisfaction. The Bridgeman and MixUp Concrete EPD presents a cradle-to-gate (Module A1-A3) declaration of product environmental impact. The EPD covers the standard grades (eight grades: 17.5 MPa to 50 MPa) of ready-mixed concrete produced by Bridgeman Concrete and MixUp Concrete at their nine batching plants. The products covered by the EPD can be used in all structures and building elements commonly found in NZ, including house-floors, commercial buildings, industrial facilities, domestic driveways and infrastructure. This EPD, issued in accordance with ISO 14025 and EN 15804, meets the criteria of the Green Star rating system from NZ Green Building Council.
